# Ported from RequestsAdvancedTests.cs.
#
# Two kinds of tests live here:
#   1. File upload (multipart) + response streaming (iter_content / iter_lines):
#      all route through the internal Requests.Send(...) with a mocked
#      HttpMessageHandler and inspect/consume the resulting Response/HttpRequestMessage.
#      Unportable — internal API + mock infrastructure with no Sharpy surface.
#   2. Session redirect / SSL-verify / proxy configuration: hermetic and reachable,
#      but identical to the property tests already ported in
#      requests_session_tests.spy. Not duplicated here.
# Net result: NO TESTS PORTED in this file.
#
# Omitted tests and why:
#   - Files_Upload_ProducesMultipartFormDataContent,
#     Files_Upload_IncludesFileContentsAndFilename,
#     Files_CombinedWithData_IncludesBothPartsInMultipart,
#     Files_MultipleFiles_AllPartsPresent, Files_TakePrecedenceOverJson,
#     Files_MissingFile_ReturnsErrWithPathInMessage:
#       drive internal Requests.Send + inspect MultipartFormDataContent on the captured
#       request — not reachable / not hermetic.
#   - IterContent_* (6) and IterLines_* (4): require a streaming Response obtained from
#     internal Requests.Send with a mock handler — not reachable.
#   - ModuleLevel_AllowRedirects_False/Verify_False/Both (3): the public Requests.Get
#     path with no mock makes a real connection attempt to an invalid host — requires
#     network connectivity, not hermetic.
#   - Session_AllowRedirects_*, Session_MaxRedirects_* (incl. RejectsZeroOrNegative),
#     Session_Verify_*, Session_Proxies_*: hermetic + reachable, but already ported in
#     requests_session_tests.spy (the RejectsZeroOrNegative variant is itself omitted
#     there because the setter throws ArgumentOutOfRangeException, which Sharpy does not
#     expose as a catchable ValueError).

import requests
